To conduct finite element vibration analysis of circular plates with preloadings, a principle of virtual work is employed first to determine the stresses induced:
(1)0=∫t[∫vol[σrδɛr+σθδɛθ+σzδɛz+τzθδγzθ   +τrzδγrz+τrθδγrθ]dv   -∫A(frδu+fθδv+fzδw)dA]dt
where u,v,w are displacements and fr,fθ,and fz are preloadings in the radial, circumferential, and thickness directions of circular plates, and r, θ, z are the corresponding coordinates when a cylindrical coordinate system is used. Substituting the following strain-displacement relations and stress-strain relations into equation (1)
(2){σrσθσzτzθτrzτrθ}=[c11c12c13000c12c22c23000c13c23c33000000c44000000c55000000c66]
{ɛr=∂u∂rɛθ=ur+1r∂v∂θɛz=∂w∂zγzθ=∂v∂z+1r∂w∂θγrz=∂u∂z+∂w∂rγrθ=1r∂u∂θ+∂v∂r-vr}
where cij is compliance coefficient of isotropic materials, which are considered in the present study. Using standard finite element procedures, the system equation is obtained after assembling all the elemental equations:
(3)[K]{X}={F}
where [K] and {F} are stiffness matrix and force vector of the loaded plate. {X} is the nodal displacement vector to be derived. To calculate the initial stresses induced by preloading, the obtained nodal displacements {X} are used to calculate the strains by differentiations and interpolations, and then the stresses with the constitutive equations. The obtained initial stresses are denoted as σr*,σz*,σθ*,τzθ*,τrθ*,τrz* which change the stiffness of the circular plates via their products with the corresponding nonlinear strains:
(4){ɛrNɛzNɛθNγzθNγrθNγrzN}={12(∂u∂r)2+12(∂v∂r)2+12(∂w∂r)212(∂u∂z)2+12(∂v∂z)2+12(∂w∂z)212r2((∂u∂θ)2+(∂v∂θ)2+(∂w∂θ)2-2v∂u∂θ-2u∂v∂θ+v2+u2)   1r∂u∂θ∂u∂z+1r∂v∂θ∂v∂z+1r∂w∂θ∂w∂z-vr∂u∂z+ur∂v∂z   1r∂u∂r∂u∂θ+1r∂v∂r∂v∂θ+1r∂w∂r∂w∂θ+ur∂v∂r-vr∂u∂r∂u∂r∂u∂z+∂v∂r∂v∂z+∂w∂r∂w∂z}

Incorporating equation (5) into the finite element formulation leads to the following elemental equation:
(6)[[m11][m12][m13][m21][m22][m23][m31][m32][m33]]{{U··}{V··}{W··}}+[[[k11][k12][k13][k21][k22][k23][k31][k32][k33]]+[[g11][g12][g13][g21][g22][g23][g31][g32][g33]]]{{U}{V}{W}}={0}
where submatrices [mij], [kij], and [gij] constitute the mass, stiffness, and geometric matrices, respectively. The geometric matrix arises from the inclusion of the initial stresses due to preloading on the circular plates. {U}T=[u1u2…up], {V}T=[v1v2…vp], and {W}T=[w1w2…wp] are the element nodal displacement vectors, p is the number of nodes in an element.
